modules.description: Tracks and displays frames per second (FPS) in a graphics application. It uses mutable references to store the last calculated FPS value, frame count, and time intervals, updating them dynamically during runtime. The module provides functions to update the FPS counter and render the current FPS as text using a Cairo graphics context.

This module combines 2D rendering with Cairo, regex-based string manipulation, and HTTP client features to build interactive graphics applications. It manages state and rendering contexts through a custom result monad, supporting dynamic content loading, frame-rate control, and robust error handling. The FPS submodule tracks and displays frame rates using mutable state, updating counters and rendering text dynamically during rendering loops. Together, they enable real-time visualizations with performance monitoring and external resource integration.
